# Firebase Patterns

## Auth Flow
- Google Sign-In via **redirect** (not popup — popup triggers COOP errors in Chrome)
- Use `signInWithRedirect` + `getRedirectResult`, never `signInWithPopup`
- Auth state managed by `onAuthStateChanged` listener in `useAuth` hook
- User profile auto-synced to Firestore via `syncUser` Cloud Function on first login

## Firestore Security Rules
- Users can only read/write their own document: `request.auth.uid == resource.data.uid`
- Hobby collection is read-only for non-admins
- Test rules with the Firebase Emulator before deploying

### Common Rules Bug
If you get `mismatched input '{'` in Firestore rules, it's usually a stray character at the top. Select all, delete, and repaste clean.

## Firestore Data Model
```
users/{uid}
  ├── savedHobbies/{hobbyId}    (subcollection)
  └── fields: uid, email, displayName, photoURL, preferences, onboardingCompleted

hobbies/{hobbyId}
  └── fields: title, description, category, difficulty, tags[], imageUrl, rating, reviewCount

categories/{categoryId}
ratings/{uid_hobbyId}
reviews/{reviewId}
```

## Frontend Firebase Init
`web/src/services/firebase.ts` conditionally initializes Firebase only when `VITE_FIREBASE_*` env vars are present. Check `isFirebaseConfigured` before any Firebase SDK call.

## Hosting
- Deploy: `firebase deploy --only hosting`
- Custom domain: `hobihobby.com` via Firebase Hosting
- DNS: A record `199.36.158.100` + TXT verification
